    "description": {
      "value": "<p>Bladesingers master a tradition of wizardry that incorporates swordplay and dance. Originally created by elves, this tradition has been adopted by non-elf practitioners, who honor and expand on the elven ways.</p><p>In combat, a bladesinger uses a series of intricate, elegant maneuvers that fend off harm and allow the bladesinger to channel magic into devastating attacks and a cunning defense. Many who have observed a bladesinger at work remember the display as one of the more beautiful experiences in their life, a glorious dance accompanied by a singing blade.</p><h3>Bladesinging Features</h3><p>2nd Level: @UUID[Compendium.5e-complete-fr.5e-class-features.tgtc6E2qpoKtgiLD]{Training in War and Song}, @UUID[Compendium.5e-complete-fr.5e-class-features.aitU2h6kQU80LHcl]{Bladesong}</p><p>6th Level: @UUID[Compendium.5e-complete-fr.5e-class-features.USUJIOOOneftQaEk]{Extra Attack}</p><p>10th Level: @UUID[Compendium.5e-complete-fr.5e-class-features.8VDnMk72yTvSlum0]{Song of Defense}</p><p>14th Level: @UUID[Compendium.5e-complete-fr.5e-class-features.mmcr3Exu8FFwB5f5]{Song of Victory}</p>",
